description:
Awesome views to the inside of the volcano, but you also can see the Golfo de Fonseca, Honduras and El Salvador. In the top there is space for 2 tends or you can hang a Hammock.
Posible to make fire.  The entrance and the camping are completely free!! :) bring enough water, the hiking is not more than 30min, but the humidity could be horrible.

@vicbybike

Traveling by moto. I paid 40 córdobas for entrance and 40c for camping, but with that price I could stay there 2 nights. You can camp in the parking, but it is much better if you walk 5-10 min down to the river and put the tent just next to an amazing clear and beautiful river. 
Hardly recommend.


@vicbybike
